Object TDmxScroller
===================

    TDmxScroller (a TScroller descendant) is the primary tvDMX object.
    It provides for horizontal and vertical scrolling of records and
    fields as defined by ATemplate --the formatting string.
    Object TDmxScroller can be found in unit tvDMX.


FIELDS
------

  CurrentField	:  pDMXfieldrec;

	Pointer to the current field's information block.  This field is
	only used by descendant objects.  It was declared here so that
	it may be accessed by TDmxLink objects.  It is initialized as NIL
	but object TDmxEditor (its first descendant) will change it to
	the first usable field.


  CurrentRecord	:  integer;

	The current record number, starting from zero.  This field is
	only used by descendant objects.  It was declared here so that
	it may be accessed by TDmxLink objects.
	It is initialized as record number zero.


  DataBlockSize	:  longint;

	Field DataBlockSize is size of the database.


  DMXfield1	:  pDMXfieldrec;

	A pointer to the first record in the field descriptor chain.
	This is initialized by procedure InitStruct().


  Labels	:  PDmxLink;

	Linkage to a view that displays heading lines above the
	DmxScroller.  If there is no such view, Labels is NIL.


  Locked	:  boolean;

	Prevents editing attempts by the user.


  RecordSize	:  integer;

	Size of each record.
	This is initialized by procedure InitStruct().


  TotalFields	:  integer;

	The last numbered field in the field descriptor chain.  Some
	fields are "Combined Fields" such as DateTime, in which case the
	six WORD types will all count as two fields (one Date field and
	one Time field).  This is initialized by procedure InitStruct().


  Vidis		:  boolean;

	If TRUE, it prevents tvDMX from resetting the current field and
	record when it loses the focus.  This should only be set TRUE
	prior to opening a MessageBox().  Altering this field will be
	useful only for buffered data objects.
	This field should normally remain FALSE.


  WorkingData	:  pointer;

	A pointer to the database in memory.  Some descendants that
	override function DataAt() may not need this pointer, although
	all of the example units and programs do.
	This is initialized by procedure InitData().



METHODS
-------

  constructor Init (ATemplate : string;  var AData;
		    BSize : longint;  var Bounds : TRect;
		    ALabels : PDmxLink;
		    AHScrollBar,AVScrollBar : PScrollBar);

      Calls TScroller.Init().
      The DataBlockSize field is set to BSize.
      The field descriptor chain is initialized by proc InitStruct().
      Virtual method InitData() sets field WorkingData to @AData.
      The maximum record number is determined by BSize.
      The GrowMode field is set to (gfGrowHiX or gfGrowHiY);
      If ALabels is not NIL then the ALabels view is linked to this object.


  destructor Done;
	VIRTUAL;

    Calls the DoneData() and DoneStruct() virtual methods before calling
    TScroller.Done().


  constructor Load (var S : TStream);

    Calls TScroller.Load().  Reads the object's fields, and then calls the
    LoadData() and LoadStruct() virtual methods.


  proc  ChangeBounds (var Bounds : TRect);
	VIRTUAL;

    Sets InBuffer to FALSE, to ensure that the entire view is redrawn, and
    then calls the inherited ChangeBounds() method.  (InBuffer is a private
    field that indicates whether text was written to Owner^.Buffer.)


  func  DataAt (RecNum : integer) : pointer;
	VIRTUAL;

    Returns a pointer to the given data record.
    By overriding this function, a program can completely alter the
    manner in which the database is organized.  It is very important
    that you understand this, as it gives programs the capability to
    access more than 64k.

    This object simply returns a pointer to the position in the database
    from (RecNum * RecordSize).


  proc  DoneData;
	VIRTUAL;

    Pseudo-abstract method that can be overridden to post-process the
    data records.


  proc  DoneStruct;
	VIRTUAL;

    Disposes of the internal field-descriptor chain.


  proc  Draw;
	VIRTUAL;

    Draws the view by calling DrawRecord() for each row in the view.
    Under certain conditions, most of the view may be copied from the
    view Owner's buffer to save time.


  proc  DrawRecord (Y : integer;  var DataRecord );

    Displays data in DataRecord on screen row Y.  It uses the TScroller's
    Delta field to find the screen's offset.


  proc  FieldText (var S : string;  var Color : word;
		   Field : pDMXfieldrec;  var DataRec );
	VIRTUAL;

    Pseudo-abstract method that is called just before drawing a field.
    The default method does nothing, but it may be overwritten to modify
    the text string or the color.

    The S and Color parameters may be modified.  Color is the actual
    screen color attribute.  This will be 0 when tvDMX is printing.

    DataRec is the record of the field that is being addressed.  A pointer
    to the field data can be found by adding the value of Field^.datatab to
    the address of DataRec.

      eg:  FData := ptr(seg(DataRec), ofs(DataRec) + Field^.datatab);

    Note that, if this object is a TDmxEditor descendant, you may use its
    DrawingField boolean field to indicate whether the field being displayed
    is currently highlighted.

      eg:  If (S = '[X]') and DrawingField then Color := Color or Blink;


  func  GetPalette  : PPalette;
	VIRTUAL;

    Returns a pointer to the view's palette.  It uses cDMX (defined in
    unit DmxGizma) as this string.


  proc  HandleEvent (var Event : TEvent);
	VIRTUAL;

    Handles most events by calling the inherited HandleEvent(), and then
    processes these evCommand or evBroadcast events:  cmDMX_RollCall,
    cmDMX_Draw, cmDMX_DrawData, cmDMX_LockData, cmDMX_UnlockData.


  proc  InitData (var AData );
	VIRTUAL;

    Sets pointer field WorkingData to @AData.  Can be overridden to
    initialize different data if function DataAt() is also overridden.
                                                      

  proc  InitStruct (var ATemplate );
	VIRTUAL;

    Uses ATemplate to set up the internal field-descriptor chain.
    This can be called multiple times to extend the chain.


  proc  LoadData (var S : TStream);
	VIRTUAL;

    Abstract method called by the Load() constructor.
    This MUST set the object's DataBlockSize and WorkingData fields.


  proc  LoadStruct (var S : TStream);
	VIRTUAL;

    Virtual method called by the Load() constructor to load the internal
    field-descriptor chain.


  func  RecNumStr (RecNum : integer) : string;
	VIRTUAL;

    Must return a record number in string form.   This method is used
    only by the reporting objects (in unit tvDMXREP.PAS) to print record
    numbers in a format specific to the view.
    It is overridden in unit tvDMXHEX to return record numbers in hex.


  func  RecordLimit : longint;
	VIRTUAL;

    Returns the total number of records in the table.  This method is
    overridden in some descendants to ignore an expansion record.


  proc  SetState (AState : word; Enable : boolean);
	VIRTUAL;

    If focus is received (sfFocused), and if the DataBlockSize field is
    determined to be different, then SetLimit() is called to adjust Limit.


  proc  Store (var S : TStream);

    Calls TScroller.Store().  Writes the object's fields, and then calls
    the StoreData() and StoreStruct() virtual methods.


  proc  StoreData (var S : TStream);
	VIRTUAL;

    Abstract method called by the Store() method.  This MUST store
    information that will allow its data to be reconnected if this object
    is loaded again.


  proc  StoreStruct (var S : TStream);
	VIRTUAL;

    Virtual method called by the Store() method.


  proc  WrongKeypressed (var Event : TEvent);
	VIRTUAL;

    Virtual method called whenever a key is pressed that cannot be
    accepted (eg: text in a numeric field).  The default method sends
    a cmDMX_WrongKey command to the Application view.


  func  Valid (Command : word) : boolean;
	VIRTUAL;

    Calls the inherited Valid() method.  If Command is cmValid, it checks
    the InitValid field to confirm nothing was lost during initialization.

Object TDmxEditor
=================

    Object TDmxEditor is the fully functional tvDMX object for scrolling
    and editing data fields and records.  Heading lines and a record number
    indicator can be attached separately.
    Object TDmxEditor can be found in unit tvDMX.


FIELDS
------

  CurPos	:  integer;

	Position of the cursor within the current field (not counting any
	extra characters in the template).


  DataAltered	:  boolean;

	Set TRUE when data is modified.


  DoubleValid	:  boolean;

	Set TRUE automatically whenever a evMouseDown event occurs.
	DoubleValid ensures that the last mouse-click occurred in a valid
	zone that the pointer has already switched to.
	If checking Event.Double directly, programs should always check
	that DoubleValid is TRUE before responding to a Double-click mouse
	event.


  DrawingField	:  boolean;

	Set TRUE while TDmxScroller.DrawField() is drawing that field.
	It is reset to FALSE when DrawField() is complete.


  FieldAltered	:  boolean;

	Set TRUE if the current field is altered.
	This is reset to FALSE by procedure SetUpField().


  FieldData	:  pointer;

	Pointer to the data in the current field.
	This is set by procedure SetUpField().


  FieldSelected	:  boolean;

	Set TRUE when a field is selected.  It will be FALSE while it is
	changing fields or when another view is selected.


  FirstKey	:  boolean;

	TRUE if a key has not been pressed yet while in the current field.
	This is used so that right/left cursor keys can act as ctrl-arrow
	keys until editing a field.


  JustAltered	:  boolean;

	Set TRUE if any of the data was altered by tvDMX since it was
	last focused.


  LockChecked	: boolean;

	Indicates that the locked-status of the current record has already
	been checked.  This is set and reset internally.


  RecInd	:  PDmxLink;

	Linkage to a view that displays the current record number beside
	the horizontal scroll bar.


  RecordAltered	:  boolean;

	Set TRUE if the current record is altered.
	This is reset to FALSE by procedure SetUpRecord().


  RecordData	:  pointer;

	Pointer to the data in the current record.
	This is set by procedure SetUpRecord().


  RecordSelected :  boolean;

	Set TRUE when a record is selected.  It will be FALSE while it is
	changing records or when another view is selected.


  RecWasLocked	: boolean;

	Indicates that the current record was locked by another view or
	application.  This field is set internally by CheckRecLock() if
	the SetRecLock() virtual function returns FALSE.  It will be
	cleared when EvaluateRecord() is called.


  RedrawRecord	:  boolean;

	If TRUE, the entire record is redrawn when DrawField() is called.
	Procedure DrawField() always returns this value to FALSE.


METHODS
-------

  constructor Init (ATemplate : string;  var AData;  BSize : longint;
		    var Bounds : TRect;  ALabels,ARecInd  : PDmxLink;
		    AHScrollBar,AVScrollBar : PScrollBar);

    Calls TDmxScroller.Init().  Sets CurrentField by searching the field-
    descriptor chain for the first non-skip and unhidden data field.
    Sets CurrentRecord to record zero.  Sets RecInd to ARecInd.
    If RecInd is not NIL, it sets RecInd^.Link to @Self and then adjusts
    HScrollBar's width (if HScrollBar is not NIL) to make room for RecInd.


  constructor Load (var S : TStream);

    Calls TDmxScroller.Load().  Reads the object's fields, and then finds
    the pointer for CurrentField.


  destructor Done;
	VIRTUAL;

    Checks FieldSelected and RecordSelected, and calls EvaluateField()
    and EvaluateRecord() if necessary.  Then calls TDmxScroller.Done().


  proc  ChangeBounds (var Bounds : TRect);
	VIRTUAL;

    Ensures that a field and record are not selected while calling the
    inherited ChangeBounds() method.  The field and/or record may be
    scrolled afterwards, to keep the current field visible.


  proc  ChangeMade;

    Sets the FieldAltered, RecordAltered, JustAltered and DataAltered
    fields TRUE.  This is method is called whenever a change is made.


  func  CheckRecLock : boolean;

    Manages the record-locking feature by calling the SetRecLock() virtual
    method when data in a record is first modified.


  proc  ClearRecLock;

    Manages the record-locking feature by calling the ResetRecLock()
    virtual method when the user leaves a record that was modified.


  proc  Draw;
	VIRTUAL;

    Calls the inherited Draw() method, and then calls the DrawField()
    method to draw the current field.


  proc  DrawField (var Field : pDMXfieldrec);

    Draws an individual field.  The displayed position is dependent upon
    CurrentRecord and the parameters in Field^.  The color is determined
    by the value of ShowFmt.


  proc  EvaluateField;

    Called AFTER each FIELD is edited.  It adjusts ShowFmt and calls
    DrawField() to redraw the field in the regular color.  If FieldAltered
    is TRUE, then the cmDMX_FieldAltered command is broadcast through this
    view's owner.  The FieldSelected field is set to FALSE.
    *see also proc SetUpField()


  proc  EvaluateRecord;  VIRTUAL;
	VIRTUAL;

    Called AFTER each RECORD is edited.  Calls the ClearRecLock() method.
    The RecordSelected field is set to FALSE.
    *see also proc SetUpRecord()


  proc  GetBlob (Num : integer; var Blob : pointer; var Len : integer);

    Can be called to retrieve data in a BLOb field, which are unformatted
    fields that cannot be displayed or edited by tvDMX alone.  BLObs are
    accounted for in a tvDMX template string with the InitBlobField()
    function in unit DMXGIZMA.PAS.
    BLObs are numbered starting from one, and independently of field
    numbers.  If the given BLOb number exists, the Blob parameter will be
    set to the address of the data, and the size will be returned in Len.
    If the BLOb number does not exist, then Len will return zero.


  proc  GotoPos (AFieldNum,ARecNum : integer);

    Can be called to move the field and record pointer.


  proc  HandleEvent (var Event : TEvent);
	VIRTUAL;

    Calls method ProcessCommand(), ProcessKey(), or ProcessMouse(),
    depending upon Event.What.  cmDMX command events that would cause
    movement to another field and/or record must first be validated by
    the Valid() method.  TDmxScroller.HandleEvent() is called if the
    event was not handled.


  proc  ProcessCommand (var Command : word;  XY : TPoint);

    Called by HandleEvent() to process command events.  Command constants
    are defined in unit DmxGizma.  This method is often called internally
    for certain keystrokes.


  proc  ProcessEnter (var Event : TEvent);
	VIRTUAL;

    Virtual method called when kbEnter is pressed.  The default method
    moves the cursor to the next field.


  proc  ProcessKey (var Event : TEvent);

    Called by HandleEvent() to process keystrokes.  Keystrokes that cause
    the record and/or field pointer to move are converted into command
    events, which are sent to the event-handler.


  proc  ProcessMouse   (var Event : TEvent);

    Called by HandleEvent() to process mouse events.  If a mouse button
    is pressed, and the mouse is positioned on a non-skip field, then
    the cursor will move to that selected field.  (WrongKeyEvent() is
    called if the cursor cannot move to that field.)


  proc  ResetRecLock;
	VIRTUAL;

    Called internally by the record-locking methods.  The default method
    does nothing, but it can be overridden to call your own database
    record-locking procedures.


  func  SetRecLock : boolean;
	VIRTUAL;

    Called internally by the record-locking methods.  The default method
    does nothing and returns TRUE, but it can be overridden to call your
    own database record-locking procedures.  It must return FALSE if the
    record was already.


  proc  SetState (AState : word; Enable : boolean);
	VIRTUAL;

    Calls methods SetUpField() and SetUpRecord() or EvaluateField() and
    EvaluateRecord() when the view becomes focused or unfocused (unless
    the Vidis field is set TRUE).


  proc  SetUpField;
	VIRTUAL;

    Called BEFORE each FIELD is edited.  May call RecInd^.DrawView(), if
    a record number indicator view is linked.
    *see also proc EvaluateField()


  proc  SetUpRecord;
	VIRTUAL;

    Called BEFORE each RECORD is edited.  This calls ClearRecLock() and
    sends a cmDMX_SetupRecord broadcast message to the view's owner.
    This method can be intercepted to display special information (eg:
    record number) or to rearrange the record before editing.
    *see also proc EvaluateRecord()


  proc  Store (var S : TStream);

    Calls TDmxScroller.Store().  Writes the object's fields, and then
    saves a the current field's position number.


  proc  ZeroizeField (Whole : boolean;  Field : pDMXfieldrec);
	VIRTUAL;

    Called when Ctrl-T is pressed --to erase data in the given field.
    Also called by method ZeroizeRecord() for each field in the record.
    All fields with the same field number will be erased if Whole is TRUE.
    The task of erasing is accomplished by filling the field with the
    byte in Field^.fillvalue.


  proc  ZeroizeRecord;
	VIRTUAL;

    Called when Ctrl-Y is pressed --to erase data in the current record.
    It calls method ZeroizeRecord() for each field in the record.

Object TDmxLink
===============

    TDmxLink is a TView descendant designed to link with a TDmxScroller
    object, or one of its descendants, to display a heading line or a
    current record number indicator.

    This object is never instantiated.  It was only written as a base object
    to write functional descendants for linking with the main tvDMX view.


FIELD
-----

  Link		:  PDmxScroller;

	Link to a TDmxScroller object, so that your descendants can access
	all fields in TDmxScroller.


METHODS
-------

  constructor Init (Bounds : TRect);

    Calls TView.Init() and then sets GrowMode to (gfGrowLoY + gfGrowHiY)
    and EventMask to evMessage.


  func  GetPalette : PPalette;
	VIRTUAL;

    This returns a pointer to the same variable used by other tvDMX
    views for palette selections.  This should be overridden when a
    tvDMX view uses a different palette.


  proc  Insert (AOwner : PGroup);

    Inserts this view into the AOwner group.


  proc  SetState (AState : word;  Enable : boolean);
	VIRTUAL;

    Calls TView.SetState().  When enabling the sfExposed state flag, it
    ensures that the Link view (a tvDMX scroller/editor) is in front of
    this view.  And if Link is NIL, it will use the cmDMX_RollCall command
    to find the first tvDMX view.


  Load() and Store() methods are implemented, but not documented.

Object TDmxExtLabels
====================

    TDmxExtLabels is the view that displays the field labels at the top of
    the window.  The Link field (defined in object TDmxLink) should be a
    pointer to a tvDMX scroller or editor view.

    This object is not instantiated in any of the exampple programs.  It
    is usually easier to use one of its four descendants:  TDmxLabels,
    TDmxFLabels, TDmxMLabels and TDmxPxLabels.


FIELDS
------

  Data		:  PCharArray;

	Text in the label string.  The label is organized in this way for
	scroller/editors with display formats wider than 255 characters.


  DblBar	:  boolean;

	Forces the Ruler-Bar to be drawn with a double-lined frame.  This
	is set FALSE in all the current example programs.


  Heaped	:  boolean;

	Indicates that the characters in Data have been saved on the heap,
	and must be disposed with the object.


  Len		:  integer;

	The length of the label string.


METHODS
-------

  constructor Init (ALen :integer; AData :PCharArray; var Bounds :TRect);

    Calls TDmxLink.Init() and then sets the Data pointer to AData, and
    Len to ALen.  GrowMode := gfGrowHiX.


  constructor InitInsert (AOwner :PGroup; ALen :integer; AData :PCharArray);

    Calls Init() with the bounds computed from AOwner, and then inserts
    this view into AOwner.


  destructor  Done;
	VIRTUAL;

    Disposes of Data, if Heaped is TRUE.


  proc  Draw;
	VIRTUAL;

    Displays Data^ as field labels on the top line of the view, while
    accounting for the horizontal offset (Link^.Delta.X).  The bottom
    line displays the "ruler" --a horizontal line with field delimiters--
    in alignment with TDmxScroller derivative that is normally displayed
    below it.  This was improved in version tvDMX 2.x to reverse the
    order if this view is below Link, and display the field labels on the
    bottom row.  Override this method if the view has more than two lines.


  proc  DrawRuler (Upper, AtLimit : boolean);

    Normally used with (Upper=TRUE) and (AtLimit=FALSE) to display a line
    of field delimiters (see Draw() method above) on the lowest line of
    the view.  This would be a double line if AtLimit was TRUE.  And it
    would be displayed on the top row if Upper was FALSE.


  proc  HandleEvent (var Event : TEvent);
	VIRTUAL;

    Calls the inherited HandleEvent() method.
    Handles evMouseDown events by sending either a cmDMX_Up or cmDMX_Down
    command, depending upon the position of this view relative to Link.
    This way, clicking on the upper label line would move the tvDMX cursor
    up one record.
    cmDMX_ScrollBarChanged broadcast events (from the Link view) cause this
    view to redraw in its new position.  cmDMX_FixSize broadcasts are
    handled by reducing the width of its owner.


  proc  SetState (AState : word;  Enable : boolean);
	VIRTUAL;

    Calls TDmxLink.SetState().  When enabling the sfExposed state flag, it
    sets GrowMode to a value depending upon whether Link is above or below
    this view.


  Load() and Store() methods are implemented, but not documented.

Objects TDmxLabels, TDmxFLabels, TDmxMLabels and TDmxPxLabels
=============================================================

    Object TDmxLabels is a descendent of TDmxExtLabels that initializes its
    Data and Len fields, using a pointer to a string.

    Object TDmxFLabels stores its label string on the heap.

    Object TDmxMLabels is initialized with a PSItem pointer to a chain of
    strings.  This object concatenates the string into a contiguous list of
    characters.  Use this derivative when your tvDMX view must scroll more
    than 255 characters.  (See proc InitTSItemFields() in unit DMXGIZMA.)

    Object TDmxPxLabels is used with the TDmxParadox object (in unit PxDMX).


    Each of these objects has an additional constructor InitInsert() that
    can assign its own bounds at the top of a window (given in a parameter
    called AOwner).  They INSERT themselves directly into a given window.

    These derived objects have no new fields.


OBJECTS
-------

  constructor TDmxLabels.Init (DataStr : pstring;  var Bounds : TRect);
  constructor TDmxLabels.InitInsert (AOwner : PGroup;  DataStr : pstring);

    Calls TDmxExtLabels.Init() and then sets the Data pointer to the first
    character in DataStr^, and sets Len to the length of DataStr^.


  constructor TDmxFLabels.Init (LabelStr : string;  var Bounds : TRect);
  constructor TDmxFLabels.InitInsert (AOwner : PGroup;  LabelStr : string);

    Calls TDmxExtLabels.Init() and then sets Len to the length of LabelStr.
    It allocates space for the characters in Data and sets the Data pointer
    accordingly.


  constructor TDmxMLabels.Init (Labels : PSItem;  var Bounds : TRect);
  constructor TDmxMLabels.InitInsert (AOwner : PGroup;  Labels : PSItem);

    Calls TDmxExtLabels.Init() and then sets the Data pointer to AData, and
    Len to ALen.  GrowMode := gfGrowHiX.


  constructor TDmxPxLabels.Init (var Bounds : TRect);
  constructor TDmxPxLabels.InitInsert (AOwner : PGroup);

    Calls TDmxExtLabels.Init() and sets Heaped to TRUE.  The PxDMX unit's
    InitializingPxLabels pointer is set to @Self.  The TDmxParadox view will
    fill in the field names as while initializes.


Objects TDmxRecInd and TDmxExpRecInd
====================================

    TDmxRecInd displays a record number indicator.  This is overridden by
    object TDmxExpRecInd in unit tvDMXBUF to display both a current record
    number and the total number of records.

    These derivatives have no special fields.


METHODS
-------

  constructor Init (Bounds : TRect;  Len : integer);

    Calls TDmxLink.Init (Bounds), sets GrowMode to (gfGrowLoY + gfGrowHiY)
    and sets EventMask to evMessage.


  constructor InitInsert (AOwner : PGroup; Len : integer);

    Calls Init() with the bounds computed from AOwner, and then inserts
    this view into AOwner.


  proc  Draw;
	VIRTUAL;

    Draws the record number indicator using Link^.CurrentRecord.
    Object TDmxExpRecInd also displays the number of records beside
    the current record number.


  proc  HandleEvent (var Event : TEvent);
	VIRTUAL;

    Calls the inherited HandleEvent() method.  For evMouseDown events,
    it sends a cmDMX_RecIndClicked message to the Application view.  (Some
    applications may use that to display a "Go to Record" dialog box.)


  proc  SetState (AState : word; Enable : boolean);
	VIRTUAL;

    Hides the view while dragging or inactive.


